and biology.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C04C3F7BB3AC85D7CB2FAF629E9CB5A" authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Barnes" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[502,667,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hueco">
<emphasis id="B9706466BB3AC85D7CB2FAF629E9CB5A" box="[502,667,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="248">Hypotrix hueco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="49C07696BB3AC85D7962FAF52BB6CB36" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="23" pageNumber="248">Arizona</collectingRegion>
. Collecting dates range from mid-June to mid-August.
</paragraph>
